com.karusmc.xmc.xml.nodes

Class GenericNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.karusmc.xmc.xml.nodes.GenericNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Node

    public class GenericNode
extends Object
implements Node
    Represents a generic XML node which loops through the events and delegates parsing to registered child nodes and tags accordingly, used by Parser.

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public void parse(XMLEventReader reader,
                  XMCommand command)
           throws XMLStreamException
        Loops through the specified XMLEventReader and handle each XMLEvent instance. The loop is/should be self-terminating. First checks if a registered node with the specified name exists, followed by registered tags. Otherwise ignores the XMLEvent.
        Specified by:
        parse in interface Node
        Parameters:
        reader - the XMLEventReader to loop through
        command - the command used.
        Throws:
        XMLStreamException - if an error occurred while looping through the specified XMLEventReader
